reviews.review_text: UK This recording is crisp & clear. Great show. Jerry is definitely juiced up and giving all he’s got to the audience! He might be fired up from having an interview with a writer who is purposely trying to ruffle Jerry’s feathers. The writer clearly not a fan of the Dead’s more into punk and probably heavy metal. Still a riveting interview. Jerry handled this writer with more respect than was deserved. I couldn’t help but think how would Johnny Rotten react in an interview with a writer who was into prog rock and the Dead? Interesting to note that Jerry revered Gary Numan (who’s song Cars is still awesome) and loves Elvis Costello and Dire Straits. Read the interview: http://deadsources.blogspot.com/2021/04/march-20-1981-jerry-garcia-interview.html
